<HEADLINE> Sandal Trees Losing Quickly in C. Tanzania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, June 20 (Xinhua) -- Sandal trees in a central
Tanzania district are losing quickly because they are highly
demanded for perfume production.
</P>
<P>
The cutting down of sandal trees has increased greatly due to
high demand of its roots in Europe and Arabic countries, Shihata
news agency reported Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The roots of the trees in the Kondoa District in central
Tanzania's Dodoma Region are used as raw materials for production
of various perfumes, the news agency quoted Justina Mangao, a
local environmental networking officer, as saying. But it did
not say when Mangao made her remarks.
</P>
<P>
Mangao said the trees have been chopped down for a long time
at Gubali, Choka, Polisa and Hachwi villages in Kondoa district
and are sold at high prices.
</P>
<P>
Felling of sandal trees has posed threats to environment in
the district, the official said recently.
</P>
<P>
She said trucks are used to transport the trees and its roots
to the border areas for exports.
</P>
<P>
However, Mangao didn't mention how per ton much the trees and
their roots are sold. 
</P>
</TEXT>
