<HEADLINE> Egypt to Cut Oil Output </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, June 20 (Xinhua) -- Egypt said Saturday that it will cut
oil output by 20,000 barrels per day as of July 1 in a bid to help
stabilize the world oil prices.
</P>
<P>
Egyptian Oil Minister Hamdi Ali Abdel Wahab Al-Banbi said that
his country will reduce the output to 830,000 barrels per day.
</P>
<P>
Though Egypt is not a member of the Organization of Petroleum
Exporting Countries (OPEC), the planned cut is aimed at supporting
the efforts made by OPEC members, Al-Banbi said.
</P>
<P>
A number of OPEC members have decided to slash their oil output
to help shore up the world oil prices. And the OPEC is to hold a
session on Wednesday to look into the oil price plunge in the past
months due to overproduction of the oil producers.
</P>
<P>
The income of the oil and gas sector accounts for about
one-fourth of Egypt's revenues. 
</P>
</TEXT>
