<HEADLINE> Mexico Force Belgium to 2-2 Draw </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BORDEAUX, France, June 20 (Xinhua) -- Mexico forced a 2-2 tie with
Belgium on a booming goal from Cuauhtemoc Blanco in group E of the
World Cup finals here on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
After trailing 2-1, Blanco equalized in the 62th minute when the
Necaxa striker netted with a left-foot volley on a Ramon Ramirez pass
from left.
</P>
<P>
Marc Wilmots gave Belgium a 1-0 first-half lead in the 43th minute
when he deflected home a Luis Oliveira corner kick with his waist,
taking the men advantage over the 10-men Mexico.
</P>
<P>
Pavel Pardo had been sent off the field in the 28th minute by
referee Hugh Dallas.
</P>
<P>
Schalke 04 midfielder Wilmots found the net again five minutes into
the second half, making a lone run into the box before chipping the
ball past Mexican keeper Jorge Campos.
</P>
<P>
But the Mexicans reduced the margin in the 56th minute when Alberto
Garcia Aspe converted a penalty kick awarded after Belgian substitute
Gert Verheyen made a foul in the area.
</P>
<P>
The two sides then played on a level ground as Verheyen was sent
off for the foul but the Danes gradually waned in the scorching
Bordeaux sun at Stade Lescure.
</P>
<P>
The Central Americans turned the tide to dominate the rest of the
game after the Blanco gaol, but the Belgians managed to hold out.
</P>
<P>
Mexico now lead the group with four points from one win and one
draw, followed by Belgium at two points from two draws.
</P>
<P>
The Netherlands, which will play against winless South Korea in
their second match later Saturday, have one point. 
</P>
</TEXT>
