<HEADLINE> France Denies Soldiers Captured by Guinea-Bissau </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 20 (Xinhua) -- France denied on Saturday that seven
French soldiers had been captured by the rebels of Guinea-Bissau who
have been fighting government forces since June 7.
</P>
<P>
"We deny these reports broadcast by the rebels," said a
spokesman of the French Foreign Ministry.
</P>
<P>
He was referring to a declaration by a rebel leader to a
Portuguese radio that seven French soldiers were captured two
weeks ago.
</P>
<P>
Commander Milciades Gomes Fernandes of the rebel force told the
TSF private radio in Lisbon on Friday that seven white French
soldiers armed with machineguns were captured in the fighting.
</P>
<P>
France has 1,200 troops in Senegal, a neighboring country of
Guinea-Bissau.
</P>
<P>
Senegalese troops have reportedly been involved in the the
fighting in Bissau.  
</P>
