<HEADLINE> France to Hold State Funeral for Legendary Sailor </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 20 (Xinhua) -- France will hold a state funeral on
Sunday in the Brittany port city of Brest for its legendary boat
sailor Eric Tabarly, who died on June 13 after falling into the
sea from sailing boat near Wales.
</P>
<P>
President Jacques Chirac will attend the funeral, which will
consist of a ceremony at a national navy school, a religious
ceremony, a salute by several gun ships off the shore and a
military parade in honor of him.
</P>
<P>
Tabarly was the thrice champion of the Trans-Atlantic Sailing
Boat Tournament organized by Britain and is regarded as a rare
ocean-sailing genius of France.
</P>
<P>
He was sometimes called "De Gaulle on the Land" because of his
contribution to the ocean-sailing experience and sailing sports of
France.  
</P>
</TEXT>
