<HEADLINE> EU Recalls Ambassadors to Belarus in Diplomatic </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, June 20 (Xinhua) -- Germany and other four European Union
countries have decided to recall its ambassadors to Belarus after
a row with the Belarus government over a diplomatic compound in
the capital city of Minsk, German press reports said Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The German Foreign Ministry confirmed Saturday that Germany's
ambassador to Belarus, Horst Winkelmann, had been recalled from
his post. Meanwhile, Bonn had also asked Belarus Ambassador Pyotr
Belyayev to leave the country.
</P>
<P>
The German news agency DPA quoted British diplomatic sources in
Minsk as saying that the envoys of Britain, France, Germany,
Greece and Italy would leave Belarus on Monday for an indefinite
period of time.
</P>
<P>
The United States has already withdrawn its ambassador to
Belarus due to the same dispute which arose after Belarus'
government last week ordered the diplomats to leave the compound
in the Drozdy Park of Minsk so that plumbing repairs could be
carried out.
</P>
<P>
German press reports said that in a bid to evict the diplomats
from the compound, ambassadors' cars going to their private
residences in the compound were stopped by Belarus police for
passport checks. Meanwhile, roads to the compound were also
blocked by repair works.
</P>
<P>
In a statement issued in Bonn on Saturday, German Foreign
Minister Klaus Kinkel called Minsk's action "unprecedented in the
history of diplomacy" and warned that it would turn the country
further into diplomatic isolation.  
</P>
</TEXT>
