<HEADLINE> Yemen Supports Efforts to Solve Conflicts Between </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANAA, June 20 (Xinhua) -- Yemeni President Ali Abdullah Saleh
Saturday reiterated support for all efforts aimed at stopping the
armed conflicts between Eritrea and Ethiopia, the Yemeni News
Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
During a meeting with Libyan Secretary of Arab Unity Gomaa
al-Mahdi al Fazani, Saleh called on Eritrea and Ethiopia to solve
their border disputes through peaceful means to avoid the dangers
and miseries caused by war.
</P>
<P>
The Libyan official arrived here on Friday for a two-day
visit. During the meeting, he briefed Saleh on the initiative
offered by Libya on behalf of the Saharan countries to solve the
conflicts between Eritrea and Ethiopian.
</P>
<P>
The Yemeni leader said that a peaceful solution to the disputes
between the two neighbors of the Horn of Africa would serve the
regional peace and stability and secure international navigation
in the Red Sea.
</P>
<P>
Eritrea gained independence from Ethiopia in 1993. Ever since
then, the two countries have been in border disputes over at least
six areas. Early last month, armed clashes broke out between the
two sides for a 400-square-kilometer land, reportedly leaving
hundreds killed. 
</P>
