<HEADLINE> Germany Rallies from Behind to Tie Yugoslavia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LENS, France, June 21 (Xinhua) -- Germany rallied from two goals
down to tie Yugoslavia 2-2 in group F of the soccer World Cup finals
here on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Belgrade Red Star's teenager midfielder Dejan Stankovic opened the
scoring for Yugoslavia in the 13th minute, when he deflected the ball
with a stretching leg past outgoing German keeper Andreas Kopke after
Predrag Mijatovic floated a pass into the area from left.
</P>
<P>
German Jens Jeremies wanted to block the shot but the ball bounced
off his chest, hit the post before entering the bottom of the net.
</P>
<P>
Andy Moller almost equalized for Germany when his free kick in the
21st minute hit the right-hand post.
</P>
<P>
Captain Dragan Stojkovic, also from Red Star, made it 2-0 for
Yugoslavia by scoring in the 54th minute.
</P>
<P>
Kopke saved a shot from Darko Kovacevic but the ball slipped out of
his hand for the advancing Stojkovic to net.
</P>
<P>
Germany pulled one back in the 74th minute when substitute Michael
Tarnat converted a free kick.
</P>
<P>
The European champion equalized only ten minutes from time through
Oliver Bierhoff, the Udinese forward who scored his first goal in the
tournament on a pass from midfield Olaf Thon.
</P>
<P>
Both Germany and Yugoslavia now have four points, followed by
winless United States and Iran who will face each other in their
second group game in Lyon later Sunday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
