<HEADLINE> International Seminar On Women's Issues </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 21 (Xinhua) -- An international seminar on
women's studies opened today at Beijing University.
</P>
<P>
More than 120 female scholars from China, Australia, Canada,
the United States, Denmark, Germany, the Republic of Korea, Japan
and New Zealand are attending the three-day event.
</P>
<P>
The seminar will discuss issues such as the effects of economic
development on the social status of women, as well as their
involvement in politics, protection of their rights and interests
and and draft strategies for the development of women in the next
century.
</P>
<P>
The seminar is sponsored by the Beijing University's Research
Center for Women Issues in China and Other Countries. 
