<HEADLINE> HK Wins 1st Asia-Pacific Water Polo Invitational </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 21 (Xinhua) -- Hosts Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region (SAR) team edged Guangzhou team from China's
mainland 12-11 to win the inaugural Asia-Pacific Water Polo
International Invitational Tournament here on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
With players knowing one another very well due to their
frequent previous exchange of visits, the two teams tied on scores
 five times in the match.
</P>
<P>
Soon after the start of the title-deciding match, the younger
Guangzhou players began suffering from the loopholes in their
defense. And they failed to convert on quite a few scoring
chances, especially in the third period.
</P>
<P>
The two sides, which ranked top in their respective group
competitions on the event's opening day on Saturday, tied 11-11
when there were only one minute 16 seconds left for the match.
</P>
<P>
A well-schemed offense and one more goal scored by the hosts 25
seconds from time marked the difference.
</P>
<P>
Guam took the third place by beating India 9-8 on Sunday. India
finished fourth, followed by Malaysia and Chinese Taipei for the
fifth and sixth places.
</P>
<P>
India had offered to host the second Asia-Pacific Water Polo
Invitational, with date and venue to be finalized. 
</P>
</TEXT>
