<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Fair to Fully Exhibit Chinese Horticulture </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, June 21 (Xinhua) -- Chinese experts have approved
plans 17 provinces, municipalities and autonomous regions
submitted for projects to demonstrate the Chinese art of
gardening at the World Horticulture Fair scheduled for next year.
</P>
<P>
The Yunnan organizing committee reports that construction work
is proceeding smoothly.
</P>
<P>
The 17 plans were selected from proposals submitted by 20-odd
provinces, municipalities and autonomous regions. The Beijing
exhibition will focus on the art of imperial gardening, Shanghai
will show the vigor of a modern metropolis, Tibet will feature its
lingka (park), the Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region will display
picturesque mountains and crystal clear water, and Inner Mongolia
its vast pasturelands.
</P>
<P>
The '99 World Horticulture Fair will be held in Kunming,
capital of southwest China's Yunnan Province, from May through
October.
</P>
<P>
Some 100 countries and international organizations will
participate in the fair along with over 10,000 enterprises from
both at home and abroad. The fair is expected to attract well over
eight million visitors.
</P>
<P>
The fair will carry a theme based on the relationship between
human beings and nature in the 21st century and will concentrate
on displaying a variety of indoor and outdoor horticultural
masterpieces from both at home and abroad.  
</P>
</TEXT>
