<HEADLINE> Bangladesh Parliament Approves Supplementary Budget </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, June 21 (Xinhua) -- Bangladesh's Jatiya Sangsad, the
country's parliament, approved a supplementary budget Sunday to
meet the government's expenditure of the 1997-98 fiscal year
ending June 30.
</P>
<P>
The Appropriation (supplementary) Bill 1998 was moved by
Finance Minister Shah A.M.S. Kibria to seek supplementary grants
of 18,789.92 million taka (408.48 million U.S. dollars), and was
passed by the parliament by voice vote.
</P>
<P>
The government expenditure was well within the budgetary
limits, and the supplementary budget for the outgoing fiscal year
was of a small size, the minister said.
</P>
<P>
The government's revenue expenditure for the current fiscal
year was 145.44 billion taka (3.16 billion dollars). 
</P>
</TEXT>
