<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Mahathir: Malaysia's Economy Can Recover in 3 Months </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, June 21 (Xinhua) -- Malaysian Prime Minister
Mahathir Mohamad said Sunday Malaysia can pull itself out from the
economic crisis within three months if the country is allowed to
determine its course without the intervention of outside factors.
</P>
<P>
"If I am in full control, I can assure that within three
months, we can recover," Mahathir, who is also the United Malays
National Organization (UMNO) president, told a news conference at
the end of the party's three-day general assembly here.
</P>
<P>
However, with outside forces fiddling around with the currency
and selling of shares, it was difficult to make the economy
recover, he said.
</P>
<P>
He cited the case of the Japanese yen which went down recently.
But after the intervention by the United States, the value of the
Japanese currency strengthened against the greenback.
</P>
<P>
Mahathir also said that if the interest rates in neighboring
countries could be brought down, Malaysia's economy would be able
to make a speedy recovery.
</P>
<P>
"If the interest rate goes up, a lot of money will flow out of
this country," Mahathir said.
</P>
<P>
On market forces, he said they were not infallible.
</P>
<P>
"As far as I am concerned, market forces are motivated entirely
by profit concern. They don't care if it destroys the economy of a
whole nation or region. Market forces only care for making money,"
he said.
</P>
<P>
The prime minister said currency movement had nothing to do
with a country's economic performance or the actions initiated by
the government.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
