<HEADLINE> Unicom Growing Rapidly in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 21 (Xinhua) -- China United Telecommunications
Corp. (Unicom), the country's second largest telecom firm,
registered rapid development in east China's Shanghai
municipality, the country's leading economic powerhouse.
</P>
<P>
Since the firm set up its first branch in Shanghai and started
building the "130" mobile phone network in 1994, the firm has had
more than 100,000 mobile phone users, accounting for 16 percent of
the city's market share.
</P>
<P>
So far, Unicom has built two exchange centers with a capacity
of 150,000 lines, linking 50 cities in the country.
</P>
<P>
The branch also plans to engage in telephone businesses at the
end of this year with facilities under construction.
</P>
<P>
The paging business also maintained its rapid growth with the
number of actual users reaching 130,000 and its capacity reaching
200,000 lines. 
</P>
</TEXT>
