<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Thunderstorm Sweeps over Moscow </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, June 21 (Xinhua) -- A powerful thunderstorm and
blastery winds swept through Moscow on Saturday night but did not
caused any direct casualties.
</P>
<P>
"There are no casualties in Moscow and the Moscow Region in
connection with the overnight thunderstorm and blastery winds,"
the Ministry for Emergecies said.
</P>
<P>
The overnight thunderstorm and blastery winds fell down more
than 200 trees in the Kremlin, damaged several battlements of the
outside wall with a protective netting from the Grand Kremlin
Palace torn down, said the commandant's office in the Kremlin,
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, about 30 square meters of roofing was torn down from
a Kremlin building, the Moscow Townhall information said.
</P>
<P>
The gale winds also toppled a crane at the Northern Port of
Moscow which scuttled a motor ship.
</P>
<P>
Many cars were damaged by fallen crotches of trees everywhere
in the streets Sunday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
