<HEADLINE> Deng Xiaoping Theory Fascinates University Students (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 21 (Xinhua) -- Xu Ling, a senior at Hunan
University in central China's Guangdong Province, travelled to
Shenzhen, a booming special economic zone in south China's
Guangdong Province, for a successful job interview and immediately
returned to school to attend the weekly "Deng Xiaoping Theory
Seminar" on Tuesday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
"I'll be the first Communist Party member working for the
Shenzhen joint venture and I need to learn more theoretical
knowledge before summer graduation," said Xu.
</P>
<P>
Luo Jing, Xu's classmate and one of the organizers of the
seminar, said the hour and a half seminar is often extended to
allow for discussion between enthusiastic participants.
</P>
<P>
Chinese university students played a significant role in
spreading Marxism in China early this century and have once again
emerged as a major force in promoting nationwide studies of Deng
Xiaoping Theory.
</P>
<P>
Deng, the late Chinese leader who passed away in February 1997,
developed the theory of building socialism with Chinese
characteristics and was honored "the chief architect of China's
reform and opening-up".
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that over three million students attending more
than 1,000 Chinese universities and colleges are currently
studying Deng Xiaoping Theory. The over 2,000 Deng Xiaoping campus
study societies formed by the students have attracted several
hundred thousand members.
</P>
<P>
The first Deng Xiaoping Theory Study Society was established in
late 1993 at prestigious Beijing University which celebrated its
100th anniversary last month. China's Marxism study was also
initiated at the university in the late 1910s.
</P>
<P>
"Deng Xiaoping Theory is not only Marxism for modern China, but
also Marxism for the 21st century," according to one Beijing
University student.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980621.0085 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Deng Xiaoping Theory Fascinates Chinese University Students (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Cai Zhong, a teacher at East China Normal University in
Shanghai, said the keen interests university students have in
studying Deng Xiaoping Theory is derived from the same traditional
sense of responsibility for their nation and motherland shared by
Chinese intellectuals as a whole.
</P>
<P>
More importantly, according to Cai, students have realized that
a clear understanding of Deng Xiaoping theory will be extremely
"helpful" in the future.
</P>
<P>
"Mastering Deng Xiaoping Theory will not only provide young
students with a clear understanding of China's domestic situation
and the Party's principles and policies, but will also provide
a 'golden key' for analyzing the complicated society," said Cai.
</P>
<P>
The Communist Youth League of China (CYLC), the world's largest
youth organization with 68.5 million members, has attached great
importance to promoting studies of Deng Xiaoping Theory amongst
China's 320 million young people.
</P>
<P>
Deng Xiaoping Theory will build a "powerful spiritual pillar"
for the country's younger generation, according to a senior
official with the CYLC Central Committee.
</P>
<P>
Chinese leaders also regard the introduction of Deng Xiaoping
Theory to Chinese youngsters as the most effective guarantee for
ensuring China's reform and opening-up efforts which Deng
initiated over two decades ago will continue to develop well into
the next century.
</P>
<P>
"Our cause will be carried forward from one generation to
another and will enjoy great prosperity so long as the younger
generation unswervingly holds high the great banner of Deng
Xiaoping theory," said Vice-President Hu Jintao, who also serves
as a member of the Standing Committee of the Political Bureau of
the Central Committee of the Communist Party of China. 
</P>
</TEXT>
