<HEADLINE> Gaddafi Calls for Boosting Libya-Egypt Ties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, June 21 (Xinhua) -- Egyptian President Hosni Mubarak
Sunday received a message from Libyan leader Muammar Gaddafi
calling for closer bilateral relations and constant high-level
contacts on regional issues.
</P>
<P>
The letter was delivered to Mubarak by Gomaa al Fazani,
secretary of Arab unity of the Libyan General People's Committee,
who arrived here Saturday night on a brief visit.
</P>
<P>
The Libyan official told reporters after the meeting with
Mubarak that the message focused on two key topics: the prospects
for developing relations between "the two brotherly peoples" in
all fields, and the constant consultations between the two leaders
on the developments concerning the Arab world.
</P>
<P>
Al Fazani said he felt during his meeting with Mubarak that the
Egyptian leader was satisfied with the current progress in
boosting bilateral economic, social and cultural cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Gaddafi canceled a scheduled week-long visit to Egypt early
this month, without giving reasons. But Mubarak told reporters
Sunday that Gaddafi had a mild tonsil problem and is expected to
reschedule the trip in 10 to 15 days.
</P>
<P>
Both Egyptian and Libyan officials have denied a press report
that Gaddafi postponed the visit because of a failed assassination
attempt against him.
</P>
<P>
The official Libyan news agency JANA last week denounced the
report on the alleged assassination attempt as "lies and vile
allegation." 
</P>
</TEXT>
