<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Foreign Trade Boosts in Rizhao City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, June 21 (Xinhua) -- Rizhao in east China's Shandong
Province enjoyed a total import and export volume of 63.3 million
US dollars for the four months of 1998, in additon to attracting
close to 40 million US dollars in foreign investment during the
period.
</P>
<P>
The city's timely adjustments to the export market and
optimization of product mix have led to the steady development of
foreign trade.
</P>
<P>
The coastal city has established economic and trade ties with a
number of southeast Asian nations, with emphasis on electronics,
machine-building, cement, clothing, chemical and food processing
industries.
</P>
<P>
Many of the city's large enterprises have responded to the
financial crisis in Southeast Asia by adjusting their export
market and shifted the focus of exports to markets in Europe and
the United States.
</P>
<P>
Local enterprises have avoided manufacturing products offered
by southeast Asian nations and are instead focusing on high
technology and high value-added products with wider markets.
</P>
<P>
Plans have been drawn up for enterprises engaged in foreign
trade to increase investments to improve levels of scientific
management. 
</P>
</TEXT>
