<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Mozambique Home to 400 Refugees </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, June 21 (Xinhua) -- Filomena Chisondzo, head of the
Mozambique Refugee Support Center has revealed that the country
is now home to about 400 refugees, who take shelter in Massaca-2
refugee center in Boane county near the capital Maputo.
</P>
<P>
Filomena made the disclosure Saturday on an occasion marking
the African Refugee Day, the Domingo newspaper reported Sunday.
</P>
<P>
She noted that refugees scattered about in refugee centers in
Tete and Niassa provinces in the north are all transferred to
Boane for the benefit of management.
</P>
<P>
The refugees in Mozambique are mostly from Rwanda, Burundi,
Somalia and Angola, said Filomena.
</P>
<P>
Some refugees have already been expatriated. However, she
stressed, none of them are expelled or forced back.
</P>
<P>
Refugees have similar rights and obligations as foreigners
residing in Mozambique, they must abide by the laws in the
country, Filomena noted.
</P>
<P>
According to her, due to their limited number, the refugees
have not posed any problems to the country, neither are they
found involved in any crimes or subversive activities.
</P>
<P>
Currently, the Refugee Support Center in Boane is carrying out
several programs especially agricultural programs to help
refugees gain self-sufficiency, the official added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
