<HEADLINE> French Govt Confident of HK's Future: Envoy (1) By Feng Xiuju </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 21 (Xinhua) -- The French government has
confidence in the future of Hong Kong, said a French envoy here as
the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (SAR) is greeting its
first anniversary on July 1.
</P>
<P>
"The way the Chinese government has adhered to the
implementation of the principle of 'one country, two systems' and
adopted a policy of non-interference in Hong Kong's affairs since
the handover is indeed a factor increasing France's confidence,"
said French Consul General in Hong Kong Thierry Dana in an
interview with Xinhua.
</P>
<P>
He said that the future of Hong Kong, both in terms of
prosperity and of continuing freedom, has always been of special
interest to France, its people and its authorities.
</P>
<P>
Reviewing the days when the handover was still a long term
perspective, Dana said that France was very attentive to the
factors which would eventually make the transition as smooth as
possible.
</P>
<P>
"In 1997, the French people were very happy to see that Hong
Kong was returning to China peacefully and in full respect of its
identity," he said.
</P>
<P>
This deep attachment of France to Hong Kong is of course
enhanced by the importance of the economic ties, he added.
</P>
<P>
Noting that the present economic ties between France and Hong
Kong are very developed, Dana said that trade with Hong Kong
provides France with its largest surplus outside the Organization
for the Economic Cooperation and Development (OECD), placing Hong
Kong immediately after Britain, Switzerland and Spain in terms of
trade surplus.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
