<P>
"In my opinion," he said, "such a goal is better attained
through enriching cultural ties between France and Hong Kong."
</P>
<P>
He expressed the belief that the launching of French May
Festival in Hong Kong every year since 1993 and the selection of
Hong Kong as the first place in Asia by French organizers to hold
the Wines and Spirits Exhibition are the "clear indication of the
great importance that France attaches to this city, not only as a
gateway to China but also as a regional hub".
</P>
<P>
When asked to comment on the ties between France and China as a
whole, Dana said that such a relationship has experienced a
tremendous development over the years, not only in the economic
sphere, but even more fundamentally in the political one.
</P>
<P>
France and China went through a more difficult period a few
years ago, in connection to certain weapon-related contracts
between France and Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
However, he said the China visit by the French president in
Spring last year marked the launch of a new era between the two
countries.
</P>
<P>
