<HEADLINE> China Sets September as "Product Quality Month" </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 21 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese central government
will launch a "98 Quality Month" in September to boost product
quality and enhance the sense of responsibility of manufacturers.
</P>
<P>
A circular recently issued by relevant government departments
asked enterprises leaders to be well-prepared and work out
sound operational plans for the coming national campaign to fend
off substandard quality and irresponsibility.
</P>
<P>
The circular urged each enterprise to address one or two key
quality problems in the campaign and calls for active personal
participation of responsible enterprise leaders.
</P>
<P>
The document called for all localities to publicize advanced
experience in quality control and carry out in-depth market
investigations to seek consumers' viewpoints in the period prior
to the campaign.
</P>
<P>
The campaign will be jointly organized by six central
government departments including the State Bureau of Quality and
Technology Supervision, the Publicity Department of the Central
Committee of the Communist Party of China, the State Economic and
Trade Commission, the All-China Federation of Trade Unions, the
Central Committee of the Communist Youth League of China, and the
China Quality Control Association. 
</P>
</TEXT>
