<HEADLINE> Ethiopian Airlines Increases Annual Income </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, June 21 (Xinhua) -- The annual revenue of the
Ethiopian Airlines reached 1.6 billion Birr (about 228.6 million
U.S. Dollars) last year, compared with only 563 million Birr
(80.4 million Dollars) in 1990.
</P>
<P>
Government newspaper Ethiopian Herald Sunday quoted Yoseph
Yohannes, manager of the airlines' sales department, as saying
that the profit of the airlines now stands at 44 million Birr
(6.29 million Dollars).
</P>
<P>
The manager attributed the boosting of annual income to the
reform measures taken especially by reducing service charges,
adjusting flight hours so as to avoid delays, and the opening of
new flight routes.
</P>
<P>
Yoseph said the airlines at present has 44 international
flight routes as well as 29 domestic routes and accommodates a
total of 750,000 passengers every year.
</P>
<P>
Ethiopian Airlines has a daily loading capacity of 18 to 20
thousand kilograms of goods and deploys five cargo planes for
transporting goods from Europe and other places, the manager
said, adding that it has a total of 24 different kinds of cargo
planes. 
</P>
</TEXT>
