<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Couple to Marry on World Cup Pitch </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 21 (Xinhua) -- Ever think of holding your wedding on
the World Cup pitch?
</P>
<P>
When the question comes to Norway's Oivind Ekeland and his
Brazilian fiancee Rosangela de Souza, the answer is more than
affirmative.
</P>
<P>
They want their ceremony to be staged on the very pitch and very
day that their home countries clash in a group A game in Marseille on
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
With permission from the international soccer governing body FIFA,
Ekeland, a 28-year-old from Stavanger, will marry 29-year-old Souza at
Stade Velodrome one hour before the kick-off.
</P>
<P>
"It is unique," said FIFA spokesman Keith Cooper on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
He added the couple, both Catholic, will be blessed by a priest
after their lawyers have arranged with the local civil and church
services.
</P>
<P>
Cooper said the couple, who originally wanted it to be held at the
break during the match, contacted the French World Cup Organizing
Committee weeks ago but had been refused.
</P>
<P>
But FIFA's World Cup Organizing Committee President Lennart
Johansson and former FIFA President Joao Havelange gave the green
light on the other day.
</P>
<P>
Cooper explained the image of two people being bonded together on
pitch is in line with the theme of "football bringing people together,
love, and faternity." 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
