<HEADLINE> Fujian Records Rising Exports </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, June 21 (Xinhua) -- East China's Fujian Province has
continued to enjoy substantial rises in exports despite the
effects of the financial crisis in Southeast Asia.
</P>
<P>
The coastal province exported products valued at 4.45 billion
U.S. dollars during the January-May period, up 3.43 percent
on the previous year's period, according to customs figures.
</P>
<P>
The cities of Quanzhou, Zhangzhou and Putian recorded
double-digit growth in exports ranging from 11.67 percent to 13.9
percent.
</P>
<P>
Provincial government officials attributed increased exports to
efforts to readjust Fujian's sales strategy abroad and exerting
greater effort in the American and European markets, as well as to
expanded guidance and assistance for export companies. 
</P>
</TEXT>
