<DOCNO> XIE19980621.0104 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK Airport Railway Completed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 21 (Xinhua) -- The Mass Transit Railway (MTR)
Corporation celebrated here Sunday the completion of the Airport
Railway project, which will carry passengers between Central, Hong
Kong Island, and the new airport in just 23 minutes.
</P>
<P>
The 34-kilometer Airport Railway will provide two separate
services, the Airport Express and the Tung Chung Line. The Airport
Express is the first purpose-built railway in the world serving an
airport with in-town check-in facilities at major stations. The
Tung Chung Line will offer a fast and convenient transport link
for commuters to the Tung Chung new town, Tsing Yi Island, and
West Kowloon.
</P>
<P>
Chief Executive of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region
Tung Chee Hwa officiated at the completion ceremony.
</P>
<P>
"Completed in four years, the Airport Railway has proved yet
again that Hong Kong remains a fast moving city with a well-proven
track record of fulfilling our promises," he said. "Few cities in
the world can top our record in delivering major works project so
quickly and so well."
</P>
<P>
He noted that the completion of the Airport Railway also turns
over a new leaf in Hong Kong's railway development history. "This
is the first new railway line which we have built after the
completion of the MTR network in the urban area," he said.
</P>
<P>
Hailing the railway system as part of the backbone of Hong
Kong's efficient transport system, Tung added that three railway
projects will be built in the next five years at a cost of about
110 billion HK dollars (14.1 billion U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Jack C. K. So, chairman of MTR Corporation, also praised the
project as a great engineering achievement, saying it will again
demonstrate to the world Hong Kong's standard of excellence and
efficiency.
</P>
<P>
Altogether, 113 kilometers of tracks and 900 kilometers of
overhead cables were laid and some 3 million tons of concrete was
poured in the project.
</P>
<P>
The Tung Chung Line will go into service on Monday while the
Airport Express will start service on July 6 together with the
opening of the new airport. 
</P>
</TEXT>
