<HEADLINE> Bankruptcy, Money Suit Court Opens in Bangladeshi </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, June 21 (Xinhua) -- A bankruptcy and money suit court
was opened in Bangladesh's southeastern port city of Chittagong
Sunday in an effort to "bring back discipline" in the country's
economy, reports reaching here said.
</P>
<P>
This is the first court of its kind established in the city,
the country's commercial center.
</P>
<P>
The basic objective of the court was not to create panic among
business entrepreneurs, but to restore a healthy and sound
discipline in the banking sector, Abdul Matim Khasru, minister for
law, justice and parliamentary affairs, said at the inauguration
ceremony.
</P>
<P>
Chittagong is the power house of the economic activities of the
country, and is the second city to have bankruptcy and money suit
courts following the capital city Dhaka.
</P>
<P>
Default loans in Bangladesh now stand at about 130 billion taka
(2.83 billion U.S. dollars), according to the minister. 
</P>
</TEXT>
