<HEADLINE> European Ambassadors to Minsk Recalled </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, June 21 (Xinhua) -- The ambassadors of five European
Union (EU) member nations were recalled for consultations and
will leave Belarus for an indefinite period, British ambassador to
Belarus Gessiaca Pearse said on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Ambassadors of Grace, Britain, France, Italy and Germany made
known their decision to leave Minsk, the capital city, on Monday
in a note to the Belarussian foreign ministry, said the Itar-Tass
news agency.
</P>
