<HEADLINE> Clinton Interviewed by Chinese Reporters-2 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Asked about the U.S. policy toward Taiwan, Clinton said he will
reaffirm to the Chinese leaders during his visit the commitments
the U.S. side has made to the Chinese side. In particular, he
said, he will reaffirm that the United States will stick to its
"One China" policy and will abide by the principles embodied in
the three communiques signed between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
On the financial crisis in Asia, President Clinton said the
cooperation between the United States and China is more important
than ever before, as indicated in the economic situations and
challenges now facing Indonesia and Japan.
</P>
<P>
The president also praised the 20-year cooperation on science
and technology between the United States and China as having a
"remarkable record" in biodiversity preservation, earthquake
forecast and child health care.
</P>
<P>
He said the two countries should further strengthen their
cooperation in these areas because the potential benefits to their
peoples and to other people around the world are enormous.
</P>
<P>
