talked about the prospect of having a long and cooperative project
on the rule of law and hoped that the cooperation will keep on.
</P>
<P>
On the issue of arms non-proliferation, Clinton said that China
and the United States "have a good way of working together" and
could keep on the cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Clinton also praised China as having the oldest and richest
culture in the world.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. President said: "The United States many times in our
country's past has felt a special affinity to China. And we have
had many Americans who have lived in China, ...We have been allies
in war."
</P>
<P>
"I think there is a greater feeling for the Chinese people in
the hearts of Americans than perhaps many Chinese realize," he
said. "And I hope this trip will help us to continue to go forward
in a new and better way."
</P>
<P>
"The American people wish the Chinese people well. We want to
know more about the China of today and the China of yesterday, and
we want to be a big part of the China of tomorrow," Clinton said.
</P>
