<BODY>
<HEADLINE> India Closes 125 Highly Polluting Industries </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, June 21 (Xinhua) -- The Indian government has shut
down 125 highly polluting industries across the country, said an
Environment Ministry's annual report here Sunday.
</P>
<P>
As many as 1,551 large and medium industries had been
identified in the 17 categories of highly polluting industries and
165 of them are still in the process of installing the requisite
facilities to control pollution.
</P>
<P>
Out of the 2,137 units to whom notices were issued for not
having effluent treatment systems, 480 units have been closed and
1,457 are to be closed while the rest are in the process of
installing the system, the report said.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, quoting the forest survey of India, the
report said that the country has lost 5,500 sq. km of forest cover
since 1995 and the total forest cover is now estimated to be 63.34
million hectares, about 19 percent of the country's area. 
</P>
</TEXT>
