<HEADLINE> US, Iran Teams to Pose for Joint Pre-Game Photo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 21 (Xinhua) -- The United States and Iran teams will
mix together for one joint photo together before their World Cup clash
as a part of special Fair Play Day arrangement on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
International soccer governing body FIFA's Director of
Communications Keith Cooper said, "Instead of having two seperate team
photos, the two teams will mix together for one joint photograph,
which will have an official impact and underline the fair play theme
today."
</P>
