<HEADLINE> Nigerian Player Wants to Put Africa on Map of Soccer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
PARIS, June 21 (Xinhua) -- Nigerian Victor Ikpeba, who scored
the winner against Bulgaria to put Nigeria through to the round of
16, said he believed Nigeria could put African football on the map
at the World Cup.
</P>
<P>
Ikpeba, the African Footballer of the Year, said:"Everyone was a
bit tense before the Spain game but we did very well and to beat
Spain and Bulgaria shows how much African football has improved."
</P>
<P>
"I am delighted to have scored my first goal in the World Cup
but it was a tremendous effort by the whole team and we deserved to
qualify." Ikpeba said.
</P>
<P>
Nigerian defender Taribo West agreed with Ikpeba:"We hope to get
to the final and that's the objective of us all." 
</P>
</TEXT>
