<HEADLINE> Sampaio's Goal the Fastest So Far </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
PARIS, June 21 (Xinhua) -- Brazilian Cesar Sampaio's goal at
3:48 is the fastest so far after ten days and nearly 30 matches at
the World Cup finals.
</P>
<P>
Sampaio scored the goal in the match between Scotland and Brazil
in the World Cup opening match on June 10. If his early success
remains unbeaten then he will win the Fastest Goal Award set up by
FIFA and the World Cup organisers.
</P>
<P>
FIFA sets up the award to encourage attacking play.
</P>
<P>
In the list of the fastest World Cup goals, there are some big
names. Bryan Robson of England scored at the 27th second in 1982,
Bernard Lacombe beat Italian goal-keeper Dino Zoff just 37 seconds
into the match. The record is a 15th second goal scored by Vaclav
Masek in the match between Cezchoslovakia and Mexico in 1962. 
</P>
</TEXT>
