<HEADLINE> Precision Air to Introduce Flights to Four Areas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, June 21 (Xinhua) -- A Tanzanian airline,
Precision Air, will introduce flights to Njombe, Mbeya, Mafia and
Pemba in Tanzania in a bid to boost tourism industry and solve
transport problems in the areas.
</P>
<P>
Sunday Observer quoted Joy Nyabongo, commercial manager for
the airline, as saying that introduction of the new routes comes
at a time when the market demands in the four areas are rising.
</P>
<P>
Nyabongo said in north Tanzania's Arusha Region on Saturday
that the areas were once being served by Air Tanzania Twin Otters
which is now no longer there.
</P>
<P>
Precision Air's flights from Dar es Salaam to Kilimanjaro and
Arusha via Zanzibar have served travellers well, she added.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Nyabongo said the airline is seriously looking into
the possibility of introducing flights to southern Tanzania,
where tourism resources are abundant. 
