<BODY>
<HEADLINE> FIFA Issues Disciplinary Guidelines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
PARIS, June 21 (Xinhua) -- The FIFA Disciplinary Committee has
issued guidelines regarding disciplinary sanctions.
</P>
<P>
The committee decided that a single yellow card received in the
group competitions will not be carried over to the knock-out stage.
That means any player who has been cautioned only once in the first
three games will start the second stage with a clean record.
</P>
<P>
But the committee said the suspensions due to two yellow cards
in two different matches, two yellow cards in one match and a red
card received in the first round matches must be served in the
subsequent matches. 
</P>
</TEXT>
