<HEADLINE> Zambia No Sanctuary for Refugee Criminals: </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, June 21 (Xinhua) -- Zambian Home Minister Peter
Machungwa has warned that his country will not tolerate the use
of refugee settlements for the perpetration of crimes or wars.
</P>
<P>
Speaking during Africa Refugee Day celebrations here Saturday,
Machungwa said Zambia will never allow refugee settlements to
become safe havens for killers, criminals and perpetrators of
genocide, Zambia Daily Mail reported Sunday.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that criminals pretending to be refugees neither
deserve nor qualify for international protection.
</P>
<P>
However, the minister said the Zambian government pursues a
magnanimous open door asylum policy towards all deserving asylum
seekers who establish a valid claim to asylum regardless of race,
religion or political opinion.
</P>
<P>
At present, Zambia is hosting tens of thousands of refugees
from countries such as Somalia, Angola, Burundi, Rwanda,
Zimbabwe, Namibia and the Democratic Republic of Congo.
</P>
<P>
He also deplored the manner in which refugees are moving from
one country to another within the Southern African Development
Community (SADC) region without convincing reasons, saying that
the move is bound to jeopardise security in the region.
</P>
<P>
Machungwa urged the SADC members to device a way in which
refugees must be screened before they are admitted in any country
in the region.
</P>
<P>
He also appealed to the international community to continue
assisting countries which host refugees by providing material
assistance. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
