<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Major Headway in China's Institutional Restructuring (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 21 (Xinhua) -- China's Premier Zhu Rongji told
the second plenary session of the State Council on Friday that
major headway has been made in China's institutional restructuring
drive.
</P>
<P>
The restructuring program has been approved by the State
Council, China's highest governing body, and the government needs
to make its utmost effort to do a good work in job assignments and
in providing proper arrangements for redundant personnel, Zhu told
participants at the meeting which was called on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Following the principle set forth by Chinese President Jiang
Zemin that the restructuring should be done in an active but
prudent manner, all of the government departments have worked out
programs to determine their functions, structure, and authorized
size, meaning important progress in the institutional structural
reform drive, Zhu said.
</P>
<P>
According to the new program, more than 200 kinds of functions
that used to belong to various government departments will be
transferred to enterprises, organizations, and local governments,
while more than 100 other such functions will be divided among State
Council departments, 200 lower-level departments, a quarter of the
total, will be cut, and the State Council has been down-sized 47.5
percent.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980621.0132 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Major Headway in China's Institutional Restructuring (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Assignments and providing redundant personnel with proper
arrangements are difficult but important tasks facing the reform
drive, and are mainly aimed at making best use of the public
servants and improving them overall, he said.
</P>
<P>
The work should also be combined with the reform of personnel
system so as to increase administrative efficiency, and with the
increased rule of law, he said.
</P>
<P>
Preparations should be made for some leading officials leaving
their posts with professional training, and redundant leading
officials should get suitable arrangements within three years, he
said.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the work of converting corporations with
administrative functions into enterprise groups should be
completed by the end of year, Zhu said.
</P>
<P>
He concluded by saying that, although there are arduous tasks
in the reforms, the goal set forth earlier this year is attainable
as long as the government adheres to the principles and
requirements set by the Central Committee of the Chinese Communist
Party.
</P>
<P>
Vice-premiers Li Lanqing, Qian Qichen, Wu Bangguo, Wen Jiabao,
state councillors Chi Haotian, Luo Gan, Wu Yi, Ismail Amat, Wang
Zhongyu, and officials of State Council departments were present
at the meeting.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
