<HEADLINE> Zimbabwe's Flower Exports up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, June 21 (Xinhua) -- Zimbabwe has exported about 17
tons of flower by May this year, up from the 13 tons exported in
the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
The country's horticulture industry earned a record gross 1.5
billion Zimbabwean Dollars (over 80 million U.S. Dollars), with
what the farmers dubbed as "better quality flowers", the Sunday
Mail reported.
</P>
<P>
Mary Dumphy, administrator of the Export Flower Growers
Association of Zimbabwe, told the paper Saturday the quality of
the Zimbabwean rose was good and highly competitive on the
foreign market.
</P>
