<HEADLINE> Great Potential for Sino-US Health Care Cooperation: Minister (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 21 (Xinhua) -- China and the United States have
had "effective and satisfactory cooperation" in medical science,
technology and public health work since 1979 when the two sides
signed the first agreement in this regard right after the two
countries forged diplomatic relations, top Chinese health official
said here today.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with Xinhua, Zhang Wenkang, Chinese Minister of
Health, said: "The renewal of the agreement, which coincides with
President Bill Clinton's upcoming visit to China, shows that the
governments of the two countries support and value the
cooperation between the two sides in this regard and this will
surely open greater prospects for such cooperation."
</P>
<P>
In the past ten years and more, medical sectors of the two
countries have had cooperation in the fields ranging from
infectious and parasitic diseases, cancers to cardiovascular
diseases, public health, and medical services.
</P>
<P>
Through cooperation, the Chinese side has trained a large
number of highly competent medical workers along with the import
of capital, advanced technology, and management
expertise. Meanwhile, the US side has got valuable statistics and
analyses reports on related diseases, which are of important
reference value to them in formulating preventive measures.
</P>
<P>
With the advancement of Sino-US relations, medical sectors of
both countries should further familiarize themselves with each
other's development strategy, policies and targets in this field
so as to better cooperate in specific areas, Zhang said, adding
such mutual understanding is still not adequate so far.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980621.0140 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Great Potential for Sino-US Health Care Cooperation: Minister (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
China and the U.S., respectively the world's largest developing
country and the world's largest developed country, possess immense
cooperative potentials in the medical and health care fields.
</P>
<P>
"At a time when the 21st century is approaching, we hope that
on the basis of equality, mutual benefit and share of successes,
both sides should push Sino-U.S. cooperation in this sector to a
new phase, which will be more compatible to the status of the two
countries," the minister said.
</P>
<P>
Medical science can not be advanced without the development of
medical education and health care technology. Therefore, both
sides should put their cooperation focus on the high and new
technologies, medical education, basic medical research, applied
studies, bio-medical engineering, and health work management.
</P>
<P>
He suggested that a coordinating mechanism be set up for
personnel exchange programs in the medical science and technology,
in addition to frequent exchanges of visits of medical experts and
academic exchanges.
</P>
<P>
He also hoped that the US side would grant Chinese medical
professionals access to its research funds and projects, and
relevant US institutions would timely provide them with necessary
reports for possible cooperation projects.
</P>
<P>
"With the past experience in our cooperation, we are fully
convinced that the medical sectors of the two countries would
seize the Sino-U.S. summit as an opportunity to further their
cooperation and achieve more satisfactory successes," the Chinese
minister said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
