<HEADLINE> Chinese Military Delegation Visits Tanzania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, June 21 (Xinhua) - A Chinese military
delegation of nine senior officers arrived here Sunday morning to
explore ways of training military personnel with their Tanzanian
counterparts.
</P>
<P>
Major General Sun Qixiang, head of the delegation, said the
delegation will hold talks with General Robert Mboma, chief of
the Tanzanian People's Defense Forces (TPDF), Defense Minister
Edgar Majogo and other senior officials.
</P>
<P>
The delegation was greeted at the airport by Tanzanian senior
army commanders and Zhang Hongxi, Chinese ambassador to Tanzania,
as well as other Chinese officials.
</P>
<P>
Relations between China and Tanzania have developed smoothly
in the military field, said a TPDF statement, adding that China's
assistance to the TPDF has grown enormously over the years.
</P>
</TEXT>
