<DOCNO> XIE19980621.0150 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 13 Tamil Rebels Killed in Northern Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, June 21 (Xinhua) -- At Least 13 Tamil rebels were
killed Saturday in fierce fighting in North Sri Lanka between the
rebels and government troops, a military spokesman said here
Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Spokesman Ink Dewage said government troops Saturday continued
as planned to capture huts east of Mankulam town with rebel
resistance in Northern province of the country.
</P>
<P>
The rebels fired mortars and small arms at advancing troops,
who were backed by armor, causing heavy casualties among the
rebels.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said the infantry were effectively supported by
artillery and armor and aircraft effectively engaged identified
rebel mortar locations north of Mankulam town.
</P>
<P>
The troops have recovered at least 13 rebel dead bodies with 10
T-56 weapons, the spokesman added.
</P>
<P>
The fighting occurred after the troops continued their advance
to recapture Mankulam town in an effort to clear a route between
the north and south of the country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
