<TEXT>
<P>
SANTAFE DE BOGOTA, June 20 (Xinhua) -- The Colombian military
forces were declared "in first degree barracks concentration"
until next Tuesday, on the eve of the country's second round of
elections to be held Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Army commander General Mario Hugo Galan said Saturday that the
armed forces were deployed all over the country to guard the polls.
</P>
<P>
Approximately 11 million Colombians were expected to go to the
polls Sunday to elect a new president of the Republic.
</P>
<P>
The two candidates are Liberal Horacio Serpa and Conservative
Andres Pastrana.
</P>
<P>
The armed forces and the police have been working for several
weeks to guarantee the normality of the electoral process, the
commander said.
</P>
<P>
There have been isolated cases of threats in several places of
the country, he added. 
