<HEADLINE> Pivotals Crash on BSE Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, June 21 (Xinhua) -- Pivotals crashed on the Bombay
Stock Exchange (BSE) market during the week on sustained selling
by speculators and foreign institutional investors.
</P>
<P>
The BSE sensitive index moved between 3,434.46 and 2,961.81
before closing at 3,143.1 with a sizable loss of 204.31 points as
against the previous weekend's close of 3,347.41. The national
index also dropped by 99.49 points to 1,371.3 from the previous
close of 1,470.79.
</P>
<P>
A lackluster budget and news that the United States has
detailed its economic sanctions against India following its five
underground nuclear tests last month all contributed to the
selling pressure. Pivotals tumbled further in curb deals late on
Friday evening following reports of Moody's downgrading India.
</P>
</TEXT>
