<TEXT>
<P>
QUITO, June 20 (Xinhua) -- The first stage of the project Wharf
2000 in the Ecuadoran city of Guayaquil was started here Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The Communications Ministry said the 100 million U.S. dollar
project, to be completed by the end of 2000, covers a total area
of 25 hectares. The first phase is scheduled to be concluded in
July 1999.
</P>
<P>
Under the construction plan, several commercial centers,
restaurants, a park, an ecological center and other recreation
facilities will be built in the area.
</P>
<P>
