<HEADLINE> Clark Wants NATO to Take Military Actions in Kosovo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VIENNA, June 20 (Xinhua) -- The North Atlantic Treaty
Organization (NATO) should carry out military actions in the
Serbian province of Kosovo to end the crisis there, Commander
Wesley Clark of the Supreme Allied Command Europe said here
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Clark told the 15th NATO Workshop Seminar in Vienna that the
Kosovo crisis could trigger a new war in the Balkans, the Austria
Presse Agentur (APA) quoted his spokesman as saying.
</P>
<P>
Also at the seminar, NATO Military Committee Chairman Klaus
Naumann said that NATO would intervene militarily when necessary,
though the organization was still making efforts to resolve the
Kosovo crisis peacefully.
</P>
<P>
He called on the ethnic Albanians in Kosovo not to resort to
means of violence.
</P>
<P>
At the opening ceremony of the seminar, Austrian Foreign
Minister Wolfgang Schuessel expressed his concern about the Kosovo
crisis, saying the situation there could become the biggest
challenge to Europe's security.
</P>
<P>
The NATO seminar is a forum for politicians, diplomats and
military officials of the NATO nations to discuss issues of common
concern. 
</P>
</TEXT>
