<DOCNO> XIE19980621.0193 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Netherlands Trounce South Korea 5-0 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
MARSEILLE, June 20 (Xinhua) -- The Netherlands trounced South
Korea 5-0, the largeset margin so far in the France'98 World Cup finals.
</P>
<P>
The defeat made South Korea the third Asian team to be
eliminated in the tournament following Saudi Arabia and Japan's exit.
</P>
<P>
The only remaining Asian squad in the tournamnent Iran will play
their second group match against the United States. If they lose the
game, they will also be out of the contention.
</P>
<P>
The Netherlands started their star striker Denis Bergkamp and he
posed great threat to the South Koreans.
</P>
<P>
Phillip Cocu opened the scoring at the 37th minute and Marc
Overmars added one before the interval.
</P>
<P>
In the second half, the South Koreans tried in vain to get a
goal but the Dutch team are too strong for them. Bergkamp scored
his first goal at the tournament with a splendid performance at the
70th minute while Pierre Van Hooijdonk and Ronald de Boer scored one
each to complete the one-sided match for the Netherlands.
</P>
<P>
After the match, the Netherlands lead the group with four
points. Mexico also collected four points but have to settle for
the second place as the Dutch team have a better goal difference.
</P>
<P>
The Netherlands will play Mexico to decide the top team of the
group while Belgium, which have two points from two draws, still
have the qualifying chance as they will take on pointless South
Korea. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
