<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Three Sent to Hospital as Heat Hits Stade Lescure </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BORDEAUX, June 20 (Xinhua) -- Three people was sent to hospital for
heatstroke at Saturday's soccer World Cup game between Belgium and
Mexico, police said on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
About 100 others were also treated in an afternoon that saw
temperature rising to 37 degrees Centigrade.
</P>
<P>
Belgian coach Georges Leekens said his players had lost four
kilograms after the 2-2 draw.  
</P>
</TEXT>
